title: Instafamous Model Max Emerson: New York vs. Asia

json.text: Kristen Van Nest: Hi, I'm Kristen here with FOREO.
I'm here with Max Emerson.
Max Emerson: Hey!
Kristen: Instagram celebrity and one of our models at our shoot.
Thank you for coming and talking to us.
Max: Thank you for having me, this is so much fun.
Kristen: So, you travel a lot for modeling, what is the favorite place that you've been?
Max: I don't know, it's kind of like a top five, I have a favorite place for every thing.
The most beautiful place, I think, is Australia.
Just the natural stuff, like the beaches and...
Kristen: Terrifyingly large animals.
Max: Yeah, I mean if you're not in danger for your life, you're not really having a good time.
I think the most fun I've ever had was in Shanghai, I was there for a summer, and that
was just absolutely nuts.
Me and Asia, it's kind of a dangerous combination.
I love New York, I love having a relationship with that place; I've got a place in Williamsburg.
I'm from Miami, so nothing's going to beat Florida, ever.
Our ritual every Christmas is to go surfing.
Kristen: That's not bad, not a bad life.
Max: Yeah, it's a whole list of places.
My favorite city is probably Tokyo because it's just like one giant circus.
What about you?
Kristen: For me, that's hard, I'd say beach-wise I like San Sebasti√°n, in Spain. City-wise, New York,
just because there's so many places to shop and there's just so many crazy people
that are always entertaining.
Max: That's fair.
Max: And you're butted up against them, too, you're always in the same subway car.
Kristen: The craziest thing happens, and no one pays attention to it because it's completely normal.
Max: Which is nice, because I'm always in my underpants in public on Instagram and it's nice not to
have worries about that.
Kristen: Everyone is just like, "That's normal, whatever."
Max: As long as your crew, for productions and stuff is under five people, you can totally
get away with everything.
Kristen: I feel like, for New Yorkers, it's more frustrating getting around tourists than it is dealing
with the crazy person who's doing something insane on the street.
Max: That's true.
Kristen: Tourists are so annoying, but someone could be doing some weird dance...
Max: Yeah, someone's painting the wall with feces and they're like "Only in New York!"
They have to walk through tourists in Soho and they get all mad about it.
Kristen: Yeah, yeah it's so true.
Thank you, Max, for being with us today and giving us a chance to speak with you.
I really hope the photos come out well.
Max: Thank you very much, I appreciate it.
I appreciate my little LUNA mochi, I will promise not to eat it, and I'm looking forward
to seeing what you guys name yours.
